posts.raw_content:
Spread this information around everywhere on social media and share it with Pennsylvanians in these districts.

Two special elections are taking place in Pennsylvania on Tuesday, March 25, 2025:

1. 36th Senatorial District (State Senate):

Voters in Lancaster County who reside in the 36th Senatorial District can vote in this special election. The district includes Akron Borough, Columbia Borough, Conoy Township, Earl Township, East Donegal Township, East Hempfield Township, East Petersburg Borough, Elizabeth Township, Elizabethtown Borough, Ephrata Borough, Ephrata Township, Lititz Borough, Manheim Borough, Manheim Township, Marietta Borough, Mount Joy Borough, Mount Joy Township, Mountville Borough, New Holland Borough, Penn Township, Rapho Township, Warwick Township, West Donegal Township, West Earl Township and West Hempfield Township[1].

2. 35th Legislative District (State House):

Registered voters in the 35th Legislative District of Allegheny County can vote in this special election. The district includes Clairton, Duquesne, Homestead, Munhall, Liberty, McKeesport, Port Vue, Versailles, West Homestead, West Mifflin (districts 3, 4, and 15), Whitaker, and White Oak[5].

For both special elections, all registered voters in the respective districts, regardless of political party affiliation, are entitled to vote[9].

Citations:
[1] https://www.lancastercountypa.gov/DocumentCenter/View/17272/2025-Special-Election-FAQs
[2] https://36thdistrict.pasenategop.com
[3] https://co.lancaster.pa.us/elections
[4] https://www.ourmidland.com/news/politics/article/ap-decision-notes-what-to-expect-in-20233582.php
[5] https://elrc5.alleghenycounty.us/news/special-election-for-rep-gergelys-seat-to-be-held-on-march-25
[6] https://www.wftv.com/news/politics/ap-decision-notes/4I6KQJN3DVGCNBATWUN55OLV3U/
[7] https://lwvpgh.org/special
[8] https://www.pa.gov/agencies/vote/elections/upcoming-elections.html
[9] https://www.alleghenycounty.us/Government/Elections/Special-Election
[10] https://www.pa.gov/agencies/dos/programs/voting-and-elections/special-elections.html

----------------

## State House District 35 Special Election

- Date: Tuesday, March 25, 2025
- Location: Western Pennsylvania, southeast of Pittsburgh
- Reason: To replace Democratic state Rep. Matt Gergely, who died in January 2025
- Candidates:
  - Dan Goughnour (Democrat): McKeesport school board member and police officer
  - Chuck Davis (Republican): White Oak Borough Council president and volunteer firefighter
  - Adam Kitta (Libertarian)

## State Senate District 36 Special Election

- Date: Tuesday, March 25, 2025
- Location: Lancaster County
- Reason: To replace former Republican state Sen. Ryan Aument, who resigned in December 2024
- Candidates:
  - Josh Parsons (Republican): Lancaster County Commissioner
  - James Andrew Malone (Democrat): Mayor of East Petersburg
  - Zachary Moore (Libertarian)

## Voting Information

- Polls will be open from 7:00 AM to 8:00 PM EDT on election day[1][2].
- The deadline to apply for a mail-in ballot for these special elections was March 18, 2025[4].
- Mail-in ballots must be received by the Board of Elections Office no later than 8:00 PM on Tuesday, March 25th[4].
- In-person voting by mail-in or absentee ballot was available from March 4 to March 18, 2025, with extended hours on March 21st and 22nd[4].

The outcome of the State House election is particularly significant as it will determine which party controls the chamber, currently deadlocked at 101-101[2].
